recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 155  thereof,
Whereas Commission recommendation 88/285/EEC  (1) was adopted in order to propose measures to the  Member States to encourage third party financing for investments in energy efficiency;
Whereas the area targeted by this recommendation has now been covered by Council Directive  93/76/EEC of 13 September 1993 to limit carbon dioxide emissions by improving energy efficiency  (SAVE)  (2);
Whereas the Commission's assessment in 1991 of the implementation of this recommendation by the  Member States show the results to be very uneven and in some cases fairly ineffectual;
Whereas recommendation 88/285/EEC has been overtaken by developments in the Community's legislative  process and is thus no longer relevant,
